I"<p>It is also called <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicotinamide" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">nicotinamide</a>, is one of two major forms of vitamin B3 <a href="https://www.webmd.com/diet/supplement-guide-niacin#1" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">(niacin)</a> found in supplements. Today, it has been a promised <a href="https://www.sheenycare.com/active-ingredients-for-skin-care/" rel="dofollow" target="_blank">active ingredient</a> to help manage acne, rosacea, pigmentation issues, and wrinkles.</p>
